## STICKER TYPE DEFINITIONS (Critical for H2 #1)

### SELF-ADHESIVE STICKERS
- **What they are:** Pre-cut designs with sticky backing (peel & stick)
- **Material:** Vinyl or plastic with pressure-sensitive adhesive
- **Application:** Tweezers to peel, press onto nail, seal with top coat
- **Best for:** Quick accent designs, beginners, 3D effects
- **Longevity:** 3-7 days (with proper sealing)
- **Pros:** Easiest to use, no water needed, repositionable
- **Cons:** Can be thicker, visible edges if not sealed well

### WATER DECALS (WATERSLIDE DECALS)
- **What they are:** Ultra-thin designs on water-activated paper
- **Material:** Thin plastic-like film activated by water
- **Application:** Soak in water 10-30 seconds, slide onto nail, seal with top coat
- **Best for:** Intricate detailed designs, professional look, thin seamless finish
- **Longevity:** 7-14 days (longest-lasting type)
- **Pros:** Thinnest option, no visible edges, molds to nail curve
- **Cons:** Learning curve, requires practice, can tear if over-soaked

### FULL NAIL WRAPS
- **What they are:** Full-coverage adhesive strips that replace polish
- **Material:** Flexible vinyl/gel material
- **Application:** Stretch over entire nail, file excess, seal with top coat
- **Best for:** Complete manicure replacement, zero painting needed
- **Longevity:** 7-10 days (varies by brand quality)
- **Pros:** Full coverage, consistent pattern, no drying time
- **Cons:** Sizing can be tricky, requires filing skill

