## TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE (For H2 #7)

**PROBLEM:** Stickers peel off within 1-2 days
**CAUSES:** 
- Oily nail surface (didn't clean properly)
- Applied to tacky gel without removing sticky layer
- No top coat sealing
- Water exposure too soon (within 2 hours)
**SOLUTIONS:**
- Clean nails with alcohol wipe before application
- Buff gel nails to matte OR wipe with alcohol to remove tacky layer
- ALWAYS seal with 2 coats top coat
- Wait 2-4 hours before washing hands/showering

**PROBLEM:** Edges lift first
**CAUSES:**
- Sticker too large for nail (edges don't adhere to skin)
- Didn't press edges down firmly
- Top coat didn't cover edges completely
**SOLUTIONS:**
- Trim stickers to 1-2mm smaller than nail edge
- Use orangewood stick to press edges down before top coat
- Paint top coat OVER edges, not just on top of sticker

**PROBLEM:** Air bubbles under stickers
**CAUSES:**
- Applied too quickly without smoothing
- Nail surface not smooth (ridges, bumps)
**SOLUTIONS:**
- Apply slowly, smooth from center outward with finger
- Buff nails smooth before applying stickers
- If bubble appears, gently lift sticker edge, smooth again

**PROBLEM:** Water decals tear during application
**CAUSES:**
- Over-soaked (more than 45 seconds)
- Pulled too hard when sliding
**SOLUTIONS:**
- Soak only 15-30 seconds (just until decal slides easily)
- Slide gently, let gravity help, don't force

